  "footnotes": [
    "Odrysian Kingdom: The first major Thracian state, centred in southern Thrace (modern southern Bulgaria and northern Turkey/Greece); became a Roman client kingdom.",
    "Bulgar Khanate (681 CE): Founded after the Bulgars under Asparuh crossed the Danube; recognised by Byzantine treaty; converted to Christianity under Boris I (864 CE).",
    "Second Bulgarian Empire: Re-established by the Asen brothers (Peter and Asen) in 1185 after a revolt against Byzantium; peaked under Ivan Asen II (1218–1241).",
    "Principality of Bulgaria: Created by Treaty of San Stefano (1878) after the Russo-Turkish War; scope reduced by Congress of Berlin; full independence declared 1908.",
    "WWII: Bulgaria was Axis-aligned but did not declare war on the USSR; after Soviet entry in 1944, a communist-led Fatherland Front seized power."
  ]
